## 🔹 3. Structure of REST API

Every REST API has 5 parts.

| Part         | Example             |
| ------------ | ------------------- |
| URL          | /api/login          |
| Method       | POST                |
| Headers      | token, content-type |
| Request body | username, password  |
| Response     | JSON                |

Example:

Request:

```http
POST /api/login
```

Body:

```json
{
  "username": "azeez",
  "password": "123"
}
```

Response:

```json
{
  "token": "abc123",
  "role": "FSE"
}
```

QA validates response.

---

## 🔹 4. HTTP Methods in REST API

Very important for automation.

| Method | Use            |
| ------ | -------------- |
| GET    | Read data      |
| POST   | Create / login |
| PUT    | Update         |
| DELETE | Delete         |
| PATCH  | Partial update |

In HPM support tool you will mostly use:

✅ GET
✅ POST
✅ PUT
✅ DELETE

Example:

| API      | Method |
| -------- | ------ |
| /login   | POST   |
| /devices | GET    |
| /connect | POST   |
| /config  | PUT    |
| /logs    | GET    |
| /user    | DELETE |

QA must test all.

